<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="276" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">Male</emphasis>
. Length 3.12 mm, width 2.64 mm. Body elongate-oval, with long dense yellowish pubescence. General color yellowish brown, pronotum with central black spot; scutellum black. Each elytron with four black spots: the central spots fused, forming a pentagonal spot; and three on the lateral margin of each elytron, one triangular spot on the humeral callus, one rectangular spot in the middle, and one small triangular spot on the apex (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1366,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chnoodes pentagona Crotch, 1874. A – D. habitus; A. dorsal; B. ventral; C. frontal view; D. lateral. E – G. male genitalia: E. tegmen, ventral; F. tegmen, lateral; G. sipho lateral view. H – I. female genitalia; H. coxites; I. spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260664/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Figs 
<number box="[1351,1366,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A–D). Antennae, mouthparts, hypomera, epipleurum and legs yellowish-brown. Meso, metasternum and first abdominal ventrite black (
<figureCitation box="[319,388,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chnoodes pentagona Crotch, 1874. A – D. habitus; A. dorsal; B. ventral; C. frontal view; D. lateral. E – G. male genitalia: E. tegmen, ventral; F. tegmen, lateral; G. sipho lateral view. H – I. female genitalia; H. coxites; I. spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260664/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Fig. 
<number box="[372,388,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Genitalia symmetrical; basal lobe wide, half length of parameres, tapered at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1209,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chnoodes pentagona Crotch, 1874. A – D. habitus; A. dorsal; B. ventral; C. frontal view; D. lateral. E – G. male genitalia: E. tegmen, ventral; F. tegmen, lateral; G. sipho lateral view. H – I. female genitalia; H. coxites; I. spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260664/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Fig. 
<number box="[1193,1209,440,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Parameres wide, elongated, with long bristles throughout their length (
<figureCitation box="[770,840,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chnoodes pentagona Crotch, 1874. A – D. habitus; A. dorsal; B. ventral; C. frontal view; D. lateral. E – G. male genitalia: E. tegmen, ventral; F. tegmen, lateral; G. sipho lateral view. H – I. female genitalia; H. coxites; I. spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260664/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Fig. 
<number box="[825,840,476,500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Sipho sinuous, with wide siphonal capsule (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chnoodes pentagona Crotch, 1874. A – D. habitus; A. dorsal; B. ventral; C. frontal view; D. lateral. E – G. male genitalia: E. tegmen, ventral; F. tegmen, lateral; G. sipho lateral view. H – I. female genitalia; H. coxites; I. spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260664/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,512,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
G).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">Female</emphasis>
. Length 3.00–3.40 mm, width 2.40–2.80 mm. Coxites longer than wide, subtriangular; apex mammilliform, with long bristles (
<figureCitation box="[544,613,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chnoodes pentagona Crotch, 1874. A – D. habitus; A. dorsal; B. ventral; C. frontal view; D. lateral. E – G. male genitalia: E. tegmen, ventral; F. tegmen, lateral; G. sipho lateral view. H – I. female genitalia; H. coxites; I. spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260664/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Fig. 
<number box="[598,613,584,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Spermatheca C-shaped, elongated, with slightly narrowed apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,791,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chnoodes pentagona Crotch, 1874. A – D. habitus; A. dorsal; B. ventral; C. frontal view; D. lateral. E – G. male genitalia: E. tegmen, ventral; F. tegmen, lateral; G. sipho lateral view. H – I. female genitalia; H. coxites; I. spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260664/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,620,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" value="4.0">
<date box="[151,167,620,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">4</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" box="[199,772,655,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,509,655,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
